The accused will remain in custody after waiving their bail application during a previous appearance. CAPE TOWN - The case against four teenagers accused of raping a 15-year-old girl has been postponed in the Knysna Magistrates Court.The accused appeared briefly in the dock earlier on Tuesday; they will remain in custody after waiving their bail application during a previous appearance.The rape survivor was apparently lured to a house in an area known as White location in February.There she was repeatedly raped, allegedly by the four youths.The community was left outraged following the incident and is calling for the harshest sentences possible.